Language name: AKAN
Language number: 4115
Alternate names: Twi, Asante, Fante
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Kwa
Comments: Labialized palatals appear as labialized velars 
before back vowels.  Velar stops and palatal affricates 
are largely complementary in distribution but show 
contrast before /a/.
Sources: 

Dolphyne, F.A. 1988. The Akan (Twi-Fante) Language: Its 
Sound Systems and Tonal Structure. Ghana Universities 
Press, Accra.

Ladefoged, P. 1964. A Phonetic Study of West African 
Languages. Cambridge University Press.

Schachter, P. and Fromkin, V.A. 1968. A Phonology of Akan:  
Akuapem, Asante, Fante (UCLA Working Papers in Phonetics 
9). Phonetics Laboratory, University of California, Los 
Angeles.

Stewart, J.M. 1967. Tongue root position in Akan vowel 
harmony. Phonetica 16: 185-204.

Welmers, W.E. 1946. A Descriptive Grammar of Fanti 
(Language Dissertation 39). Linguistic Society of America, 
Philadelphia.